headline: BofA Names Ed Siaje President of Detroit
summary: Bank of America has named Ed Siaje president of Bank of America Detroit. As president and head of the market, he will connect clients, teammates and communities to the full power of the franchise and drive integration across the bank's eight lines of business. He succeeds Matt Elliott, who recently retired from the company.
